{
  "texts": [
    "Starting from an all-zero state, we program a time-independent, global quench under the onedimensional Ising-like Rydberg Hamiltonian (Fig. 2a, for Hamiltonian details see Supplementary Fig.",
    "3 and the Supplementary Information).",
    "Hamiltonian parameters lead to high-temperature thermalization 31, such that describing |ψ⟩ at late times requires an exponential number of classical coefficients 14.",
    "For a system size of n = 30 (Fig. 2c-e, left), we can exactly classically simulate these dynamics (Fig.",
    "2d, grey); by exact, we mean the classical fidelity, C Ψ ψ = ⟨ ⟩ sim 2, stays near unity for all times."
  ]
}